sms, science fiction, cybernetics, neuroscience, artificial intelligence research, electronic music and other digital practicesUltimately argues that fictioning is at its most radical and experimental in the expanded field of contemporary art practice"  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aArtxPhilosophy. 0aFictions, Theory of. 4aPhilosophy. 7aART / Criticism.2bisacsh1 aO'Sullivan, Simon, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z97831107804200 cprintz978147443239940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147443241240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474432412423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474432412/original  a978-3-11-078042-0  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_AD  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_AD  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK